cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the design of dynamic spectrum access in cognitive radio networks, which involves wireless communications and interference control. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing techniques, which suggest the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with interference control and spectrum sensing, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a new scheme for cognitive radio networks, which involves system design and control, suggesting the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves simulations and analysis of packet loss rates, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
